# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values.

```bash
cp .env.example .env.local
```

## Supabase

Get these from your [Supabase project settings](https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api):

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
```

## Resend (SMTP for Supabase Auth emails)

Get API key from [Resend Dashboard](https://resend.com/api-keys):

```
RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
```

To auto-configure Supabase SMTP (optional):

```
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=sbp_...
```

Then run: `bash scripts/configure-supabase-resend-smtp.sh`

Manual SMTP in Supabase dashboard (Auth → SMTP):
- Host: `smtp.resend.com` | Port: `465` | User: `resend`
- Password: your `RESEND_API_KEY`
- Sender: `TaskFlow Pro <onboarding@resend.dev>` (test; verify a domain for production)


Get these from [Stripe Dashboard](https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/apikeys):

```
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_BUSINESS=price_...
```

Create products "Pro" (€12/mo) and "Business" (€29/mo) in Stripe test mode and copy the Price IDs.

## App

```
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

For production, set to your Vercel domain (e.g. `https://taskflow-pro-murex.vercel.app`).
